{"cursor":"1409","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'threshold' is the sill of a door. In many cultures it has a special\nsymbolism: for instance, in Poland and Russia it is bad luck to shake hands or\nkiss across the threshold when meeting somebody. In many countries it is considered\ngood luck for a bridegroom to carry the bride over the threshold to their new\nhome.\n","linknr":107,"url":"Threshold_(door)","recorded":1362564676,"links":19,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Superstitions"],"headings":["Etymology","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg/40px-Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Door","Poland","Russia","Bridegroom","Bride","Old_English"]}